title: For Sale/Trade:  WWII Auto-Ordnance Thompson, PRICE REDUCED!!!
postcontent:
FOR SALE OR TRADE: I have a very limited edition, genuine Auto-Ordnance Thompson M1927A1 built in 1983. This is one of only 750 produced in a deluxe presentation finish and selectively plated with 24 karat gold, honoring the World War II three theaters of operation. Special commemorative inscriptions are engraved and gold-gilt filled on both sides of the receiver and inlaid in the pistol grip is a Victory medal.

Very few if any of the 750 produced were available to the general public as they were sold originally to the Veterans of Foreign Wars Organization and another which presented these firearms to honored veterans. Over 30 years ago when produced these came in a glass top presentation case at a cost of $3,000. The only other one currently for sale is priced at $4,000. Follow Link: http://www.gunsinternational.com/WWII-Commemorative-Thompson-45ACP-NEW-IN-PRESENTATION-CASE.cfm?gun_id=100504520

The one I am offering is number WW543 and is minus the presentation case. The overall condition is very good to excellent but has been handled and fired. Drum magazines and other accessories are available from Auto Ordnance which if you are not aware is who developed and built the Thompson sub-machine gun originally. They built these WWII presentation guns to the same specifications in a semi-auto configuration. Price is $1,500 cash or partial trade and cash. New price excludes sling. Real beauty & history. You will not be disappointed. Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  Seekins Precision Flash Hider f/308
postcontent:
Like all Seekins Precision products, the Flash Hider far surpasses standard products. The unique, tri prong design swirls hot gases immediately as they exit the muzzle, extinguishing the flame to eliminate the visible flash. Built for hard use, the prongs are precision machined from steel then Melonite coated to increase durability. Melonite also makes cleaning easy, because carbon fouling does not adhere as well to the coating as it does other finishes. The design is engineered to eliminate the annoying “ping” often associated with this configuration.

The non-symmetrical design does not need to be timed, making installation simple and hassle free, no crush or peel washers are necessary. No special tools are required either. Flats machined at the rear of Flash Hider will accommodate a number of wrench styles that are readily available.  Flats are 0.75 across and the OD of the piece at the prongs is 0.85.......

Too small for my heavy barreled bolt gun, but would be a nice addition to the slimmer AR- platform barrels.  This is NOT a muzzle brake for recoil reduction, and has never been mounted on a barrel. No trades at this time, and thanks for looking.

The famous Winchester Model 1912 pump shotgun was designed by Winchester's Thomas C. Johnson. Introduced in 20 gauge in 1912, 16 and 12 gauge guns followed in 1914. title: For Sale/Trade:  Marlin 1895 Guide Gun Prototype .45-70 Gov't. $550 OBO
location: NW Suburb, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
Marlin has been manufacturing the Guide Gun since 1998. Before Marlin started making the Guide Gun, however, Alaska gunsmiths were shortening the barrel on the 1895 lever action. The shortened rifle was great medicine for use on irritated bears in the wild. The compact firearm could pump out lead as quickly as a guide could work the lever--thus, the guide gun was born. This is one of those early conversions. The rifle itself is a pre-1998 Marlin 1895 in .45-70. The barrel has been professionally shortened. 

The whole thing is pre-Remington, pre-safety (just use the half-cock notch on the hammer), and pre-cheapening. It has the classic Marlin pistol-grip configuration and the Marlin bullseye in the walnut stock. This carbine has been carried some, but shot very little. It's a great piece to carry on a trek through the woods or to throw in the canoe on a camping trip. Call it insurance when sharing the woods with critters.

title: For Sale/Trade:  FNX-45 ***Scam Alert***
postcontent:
Hello All,

I've been looking for an FNX-45 Tactical and have run across a few scammers here on ArmsList.  Although I've reported/flagged them as scams, they're still listed here, so I figured I'd actually list the ones I've come across:

This guy is selling a BRAND NEW FNX-45 for $200 below retail cost.  He's in Florida and asks for payment right away.  When I asked for a photo with his name, phone, or email in the photo he sent numerous emails telling me he had no time for games, yet he had no time to snap a quick photo before I sent him close to $1000 for a handgun.  

http://www.armslist.com/posts/3730410/florida-handguns-for-sale--brand-new-f-n-pistols--45-acp-pistols

This guy claims his wife is sick and he needs the money for medical bills.  So he's selling an FNX-45 with an RMR.  Total value of $1,500 all for $880!  What a deal!  However, I did a Google Image search and found the photos were taken from another site here:

https://www.ar15.com/archive/topic.html?b=7&f=88&t=1335420

and here:
http://www.theoutdoorstrader.com/threads/721633-Item-Gone!-FS-FDE-FNX-45-Tactical-w-RM07-Trijicon-RMR

When confronted with this information he sent me his driver's license, told me he used to be a cop, etc...I have his name, address, phone, email, etc...Asked for money immediately be sent, Money Order ONLY!!  He normally responds within minutes to my texts and emails, but I asked for a photo with his name, phone, or email in the photo and I've heard nothing for over 8 hours.

http://www.armslist.com/posts/3768142/minnesota-handguns-for-sale--fnx-45-tactical-in-fde-with-trijicon-rm07-rmr

Then I found this ad, for the same gun (different RMR), but exact same city and state.  Coincidence?  I think not.

http://www.armslist.com/posts/3768370/minnesota-handguns-for-sale--fde-fnp-45-tactical---3--15rd-mag--red-dot-sight

Be careful guys, there are a lot of scammers out there.  I am sure more than just these, but do your due diligence before sending money to these guys.

title: For Sale/Trade:  ammo scam alert
postcontent:
Best ammo supply aka global ammo supply has posted an add for ammo at damned good prices.....upon investigating the best way to describe what they are doing is by what someone else posted about them.........


Joined: Dec 2014
 USA
  Posts: 1
 Feedback: 0% (0)
 Link To This Post
Posted: 12/19/2014 1:21:45 AM EST
BE AWARE! BE AWARE! I got suckered into trying to buy cheap priced S&W 500 magnum ammo from these douche bags !! We attempted two different one (1) box orders to check out the ammo. Neither transaction was processed. They send a "Thank you for your order. You will receive a confirmation email within one hour" message after you click on the "submit" button. We never received a confirmation email! Nothing was ever processed and no charges were charged against either credit card we used. 

But two days later, each credit card was fraudulently used by "someone" to attempt a minor "ping charge" at an on-line site called "Racing Junk" for $20.00. Neither of the owners of the credit cards placed the orders with Racing Junk, but the transaction history of both cards involved only overlaps with the transactions TO GLOBAL AMMO SUPPLY!! 

YOU BE THE JUDGE! BEING DESPERATE FOR CHEAP PRICED AMMO FOR THE BAD A-- 500 MAGNUM, I IGNORED ALL THE RED FLAGS ON THIS ONLINE SITE! 

Let my experience protect you from making the same mistake! 

This information has been submitted to the fraud departments of US Band and a regional credit union.

postcontent:

Beretta 92A1 9mm

 FAMILY:92 Pistol Series

 MODEL:92A1

 TYPE:Semi-Auto Pistol

 ACTION:Double / Single Action

 FINISH:Matte Blue

 STOCK/FRAME:Alloy Frame

 OVERALL LENGTH:8.5"

 SIGHTS:Removable Front Sight

 SAFETY:Slide Mounted Manual/Decocker

 ADDL INFO:Picatinny Rail

 ADDL INFO:Rounded Trigger Guard

 ADDL INFO:Internal Frame Recoil Buffer

 GUN CASE:Plastic

92A1: Legendary 92 Reliability with Ultra-Modern Tactical Features

The "A1" class is a specialized tactical branch of the most tested and trusted military and personal defense weapon in history: the 92FS. We started with the super-reliable 92, keeping the engineering characteristics that make it so accurate, safe and dependable; then, we added some features prized by today’s most demanding tactical shooters as well as by those wanting the absolute best for home defense or personal protection. The result is the 92A1, a pistol that is as reliable for its intended use as it is safe and user-friendly even for the novice.

Easy Accessorization and Maintenance

The most noticeable difference between the classic 92FS and the 92A1 is that this comes with an integral Picatinny rail situated in front of the trigger guard. The rail makes it easy to attach a variety of tactical accessories, including lighting systems and laser aiming devices. Also, the 92A1 has a removable front sight, meaning that you can exchange it in a matter of minutes without any gunsmithing or alteration to the pistol. Maintenance is easy thanks to the tool-free disassembly latch as well as the captive recoil-spring unit.

Impressive Firepower, Extra-Durable Magazines

Another feature that will impress you about the 92A1 is the type of magazine it comes with. This pistol comes with three 17-round magazines designed to deliver remarkable firepower out of the box while being absolutely durable and corrosion resistant. Furthermore, the magazines on the 92A1 feature a “dirt rail” along their length, which helps collect dust and grit out of the magazine while keeping cartridges clear of the magazine walls. The result: enhanced feeding reliability and super-easy magazine maintenance. In addition, the magazine well is aggressively beveled, making it super-fast to change magazines without taking your eyes off the target.

Absolutely Reliable, Designed to Last

The base design of the 92A1 is the 92FS or M9, the pistol that has served the US military admirably throughout its campaigns in the world’s toughest environments. But even in this respect, Beretta never rests on its laurels. This pistol incorporates an innovative internal frame buffer that greatly reduces component stress under firing (yes, even with hot +P ammo), making it even more durable and smooth-shooting. The best of both worlds, the 92A1 offers discriminating shooters the classic overall look and feel of the 92 (including the more traditional rounded trigger-guard) with today’s most advanced tactical features.
